@node "TechInfo" "GuidePrefs Technical Information"

    GuidePrefs has been programmed following the rules in the "Amiga User
   Interface Style Guide" from Commodore-Amiga.  This means that GuidePrefs
   uses the standards concerning user-interface design and feeling.
   Also, programming was done as much as possible in a system-conform and
   future compatible way.
   GuidePrefs was developed using Lattice/SAS C v6.2 and GadToolsBox on an
   Amiga 2500/20 with 7Mb RAM under Kickstart 37.175, Workbench 38.35.
 
    GuidePrefs requires Kickstart Release 2.04 or higher (it doesn't run on
   Kick 2.02 Version 36 in the early A3000's) and should also work fine on
   future releases of the Amiga Operating System (4.xx).

    The program has been tested successful with both the Enforcer and
   Mungwall debugging tools. This should guarantee a system-safe
   program-run. Beta testing was done under Kickstart 37.175.

    GuidePrefs was fully 'localized'. This distribution provides for a
   'nederlands', 'italiano' and 'deutsh' catalog. A CatComp .ct
   translationfile is included with GuidePrefs. If you want to
   make a catalog for your own language (french, swedish,...),
   please fill in the .ct file and send it back to me. I will compile it
   and include the catalog with future releases of GuidePrefs. Unlimited
   honour and fame is yours, because your name will appear in the About
   requester of GuidePrefs and in this documentation!!
   

    @{i}Program History@{ui}

   1.0 First C-coded release of GuidePrefs.

   1.1 -Included italian & german catalog
@endnode

